## 5.1 Part A — Short Answer Questions (3 Marks Each)

### **Q1. [KTU University Exam - Dec 2023]**
*Explain the difference between a `signal` and a `variable` in VHDL with an example.*

**Model Answer (3 Marks):**

| Aspect | Signal | Variable |
|--------|--------|----------|
| **Scope** | Global — architecture level | Local — inside process/subprogram |
| **Update** | After delta delay (process suspends) | Immediately (no delay) |
| **Storage** | Represents a wire/register | Represents local memory |
| **Use Case** | Inter-process communication, output ports | Loop counters, intermediate calculations |

**Code Example:**

```vhdl
process(clk)
    variable temp : integer := 0;   -- immediate update
    signal   q    : std_logic := '0';
begin
    temp := temp + 1;    -- updates instantly
    q    <= temp;        -- updates at process end
end process;
```

### **Q2. [KTU University Exam - May 2024]**
*List the three modeling styles in VHDL. State which is most suitable for synthesis of large designs and why.*

**Model Answer (3 Marks):**

The three VHDL modeling styles are:
1. **Behavioral** — algorithmic description using processes.
2. **Dataflow** — concurrent signal assignments using equations.
3. **Structural** — interconnection of components.

**Most suitable for large designs: STRUCTURAL**

**Reason:** Provides **clear hierarchy**, **easier debugging**, **reusability** of pre-designed modules, and **better technology mapping** during synthesis. Behavioral can become unwieldy for large systems.

