### **QUESTION B (14 Marks)** — [KTU University Exam - May 2024]

**(a) Write the VHDL code (structural style) for a 4-bit ripple carry full subtractor. (7 Marks)**

**(b) Design a Mealy machine in VHDL to detect the sequence "1101" in an overlapping serial bit stream. Include the state diagram explanation and complete VHDL code. (7 Marks)**

#### **Solution B(a) — 4-bit Ripple Carry Subtractor**

**Step 1: Full Subtractor Logic**
$$D = A \oplus B \oplus B_{\text{in}}$$
$$B_{\text{out}} = \overline{A}B + \overline{A}B_{\text{in}} + BB_{\text{in}}$$

**Step 2: Structural VHDL Code**

```vhdl
library IEEE;
use IEEE.STD_LOGIC_1164.ALL;

entity full_subtractor is
    port ( a, b, bin : in  std_logic;
           diff, bout : out std_logic);
end entity full_subtractor;

architecture beh of full_subtractor is
begin
    process(a, b, bin)
    begin
        diff <= a xor b xor bin;
        bout <= (not a and b) or (not a and bin) or (b and bin);
    end process;
end architecture beh;

-- 4-bit ripple subtractor
entity sub_4bit is
    port ( a, b   : in  std_logic_vector(3 downto 0);
           bin    : in  std_logic;
           diff   : out std_logic_vector(3 downto 0);
           bout   : out std_logic);
end entity sub_4bit;

architecture structural of sub_4bit is
    component full_subtractor
        port ( a, b, bin : in  std_logic;
               diff, bout : out std_logic);
    end component;
    signal c : std_logic_vector(4 downto 0);
begin
    c(0) <= bin;
    FS0: full_subtractor port map (a(0), b(0), c(0), diff(0), c(1));
    FS1: full_subtractor port map (a(1), b(1), c(1), diff(1), c(2));
    FS2: full_subtractor port map (a(2), b(2), c(2), diff(2), c(3));
    FS3: full_subtractor port map (a(3), b(3), c(3), diff(3), c(4));
    bout <= c(4);
end architecture structural;
```

#### **Solution B(b) — Mealy Sequence Detector "1101"**

**State Diagram Logic:**
- **S0** (00): Initial state
- **S1** (01): "1" received
- **S2** (10): "11" received
- **S3** (11): "110" received
- Output Z = 1 when in S3 and input X = 1 (sequence complete)

**Transition Table:**

| Present State | X=0 | X=1 | Z (when X=1) |
|---------------|-----|-----|---------------|
| S0 | S0 | S1 | 0 |
| S1 | S0 | S2 | 0 |
| S2 | S0 | S3 | 0 |
| S3 | S0 | S2 | **1** |

**VHDL Code:**

```vhdl
library IEEE;
use IEEE.STD_LOGIC_1164.ALL;

entity mealy_1101 is
    port ( clk, rst, x : in  std_logic;
           z            : out std_logic);
end entity mealy_1101;

architecture fsm of mealy_1101 is
    type state_t is (S0, S1, S2, S3);
    signal ps, ns : state_t;
begin
    -- State register (sequential)
    process(clk, rst)
    begin
        if rst = '1' then
            ps <= S0;
        elsif rising_edge(clk) then
            ps <= ns;
        end if;
    end process;

    -- Next state and output logic (combinational)
    process(ps, x)
    begin
        case ps is
            when S0 =>
                z <= '0';
                if x = '1' then ns <= S1;
                else            ns <= S0; end if;
            when S1 =>
                z <= '0';
                if x = '1' then ns <= S2;
                else            ns <= S0; end if;
            when S2 =>
                z <= '0';
                if x = '0' then ns <= S3;
                else            ns <= S2; end if;
            when S3 =>
                if x = '1' then
                    ns <= S2;
                    z  <= '1';   -- sequence 1101 detected
                else
                    ns <= S0;
                    z  <= '0';
                end if;
        end case;
    end process;
end architecture fsm;
```

**Marking Scheme (7 Marks):**
- Correct state definition (4 states): 1 mark
- State register with async reset: 1 mark
- Correct next-state logic: 2 marks
- Output logic for detection: 2 marks
- Clean code style: 1 mark

