## 5.3 KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning / Pitfall Callout

> [!WARNING]
> **TOP MARKS-LOSS ZONES IN VHDL EXAMS:**
>
> 1. **Latch Inference (-2 marks):** Omitting `when others` in `case` or unassigned outputs in `if-elsif` chains causes synthesis tools to **infer latches**. Always cover all cases.
>
> 2. **Sensitivity List Errors (-2 marks):** Missing a signal in the sensitivity list of a combinational `process` causes **simulation mismatch** with synthesized hardware.
>
> 3. **Asynchronous vs Synchronous Reset Confusion (-2 marks):** Including `rst` in sensitivity list = async; not including = sync. Mixing them is a logic bug.
>
> 4. **`signal` vs `variable` misuse (-2 marks):** Using `signal` for loop counters creates **infinite delta cycles** and stalls simulation.
>
> 5. **Library mismatch (-1 mark):** Using `std_logic_vector` arithmetic without `NUMERIC_STD` or `STD_LOGIC_UNSIGNED` causes **type mismatch errors**.
>
> 6. **Port direction errors (-1 mark):** Declaring outputs as `in` or `inout` wrongly.
>
> 7. **Non-synthesizable constructs (-2 marks):** Using `wait for 10 ns`, `file I/O`, `assert`, `report` — these are **simulation-only**.

